author: MICHAEL D. SHEAR
title: State Department Releases More of Hillary Clinton’s Emails
text:
SEPT. 11, 2015 Some of the emails have simply been about logistics and planning for mundane things like internal meetings. Some have also shined a light on Mrs. Clinton’s handling of events in Libya, the Middle East and elsewhere. And they have suggested the extent to which Mrs. Clinton and officials in President Obama’s White House have engaged in discussions about how to proceed on issues large and small. In previous batches of emails, many pages were redacted to block personal or sensitive information — some of which has been deemed classified — from being revealed. The new emails, which will be posted on a State Department website, are likely to be similarly edited.
